			<h1>The Ball</h1>
			<p class="body text">The Bridge of Sighs Ball will be held in the beautiful grounds of Hertford College and Catte Street, alongside the picturesque backdrop of the Radcliffe Camera and the Bodleian.</p>
			<br>
			<h3>Entertainment</h3>
			<p class="body text">The Bridge of Sighs Ball Committee is proud to announce that Radio 1 DJ, Chris Stark, is confirmed to headline the main stage. <br>
			The Ball will seek to provide entertainment to suit all guests' tastes: from DJ sets in the historic quad to more intimate musical experiences throughout the grounds. <br>
			Aside from the music, guests can expect alternative entertainment with themed acts touring the grounds providing memorable interactive experiences.
			</p>
			
			<h3>Food & Drink</h3>
			<p class="body text">The Bridge of Sighs Ball will be taking inspiration from all that is Italian.
			<br>Aside from the three-course meal that will be enjoyed by all dining guests, there will be micro eateries located throughout the grounds to ensure no guest leaves hungry. 
			<br>Guests can be expected to be transported to Venice's Grand Canal and to experience the delights of its culinary heritage. Think fine wines, indulgent gelati, gourmet pizzas, spritzs and mouth-watering pasta dishes.
			<br><br>Bellisimo!
